parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the heater control panel can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, as it fails to provide the expected heat, potentially leading to reduced visibility and compromised safety.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trapped Water and Sludge around Fuel and Brake Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the vehicle's body and frame can cause water and sludge to accumulate around the fuel and brake lines, leading to corrosion and failure of these critical components, which can result in brake failure and accidents.

water and sludge accumulation around fuel and brake lines.
